cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with a machine learning model for speech and image processing, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition and text-to-speech synthesis, which are both language-related tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the paper deals with image captioning and image production models. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is another possible category as the paper deals with speech perception and production. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a broad category that could apply to this paper as it deals with deep learning models and semi-supervised learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper deals with machine learning models for multimodal communication.
